com.revolsys.io.filter
Class MultipleFilenameFilter

java.lang.Object
  com.revolsys.io.filter.MultipleFilenameFilter
All Implemented Interfaces:
FilenameFilter
public class MultipleFilenameFilter
extends Object
implements FilenameFilter

The MultipleFilenameFilter is a FilenameFilter that can be used to apply more than one filename filter to the result. The filters can either be used to exclude files from the result addExclusionFilter(FilenameFilter) or include files from the result addFilter(FilenameFilter). For each file the filter will look for a match in the exclusion filters followed by the inclusion filters. If an exclusion filter matches the file will be excluded, if an inclusion filter matches the file will be included, if no files match the file will be excluded.

Paul Austin
